cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.HC, cs.DB 

The paper discusses improving access to digitized historical newspapers through text mining and user interface design. This involves techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL), as well as deep learning (cs.DL) for text analysis. The focus on user interface design suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) component, and the need for systematic and accurate description of newspaper content suggests a database (cs.DB) aspect.
